    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-10-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="516"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/855</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Portuguese Legation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>In replying to the Portuguese Chargé d’Affaires’ Memorandum of October 22,<note
                        n="4a" xml:id="d516fn4a">Not printed.</note> requesting information
                    concerning the attitude of the Government of the United States toward the
                    proposed plenary conference to discuss the future status of Tangier, the
                    Department of State wishes to inform him that it has taken occasion recently to
                    remind the Governments participating in the conference that while <pb
                        facs="0705" n="581" xml:id="pg_581"/> it has no political interest in
                    Morocco it is fundamentally interested in maintaining the principle of the Open
                    Door in Tangier, that is as stated in its ratification of the Act of Algeciras
                    in securing equality of commercial opportunity and adequate protection for the
                    life, liberty and property of its citizens.</p>
                <p>This Government, of course, presumes that nothing will be done at the forthcoming
                    conference to interfere with the principle above mentioned or with the rights
                    and interests of the United States.<note n="5" xml:id="d516fn5">In reply to a
                        verbal inquiry by the Italian Ambassador, a memorandum in the same terms was
                        sent him on Oct. 24.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
